.TH "fman_set_mac_active_pause" 9 "fman_set_mac_active_pause" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fman_set_mac_active_pause \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fman_set_mac_active_pause
.BI "(struct mac_device *mac_dev "  ","
.BI "bool rx "  ","
.BI "bool tx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mac_dev" 12
A pointer to the MAC device
.IP "rx" 12
Pause frame setting for RX
.IP "tx" 12
Pause frame setting for TX
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the MAC RX/TX PAUSE frames settings

Avoid redundant calls to FMD, if the MAC driver already contains the desired
active PAUSE settings. Otherwise, the new active settings should be reflected
in FMan.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success; Error code otherwise.
